reviews.review_text: my name is august... for the wharf rat alone this show gets 5 stars in my book...the way jerry enunciates the lyrics and holds the notes is beautiful.  What holds it back, in my estimation, is that the set list itself is not spectacular.  However, excellent performance and a quality recording makes this one very worthy.  Don't Ease rips along as well...
distortion on guitar listen close....although i have had the other one and brokedown on my mp3 player for a while now, i have removed them only due to the distorion when jer hits the high notes

Powerful eyes and other one Not going to be long-winded here. This is a great show and I am sure you will agree this is worth listening to. Eyes is ripping and the other one I think is one of the best I have heard so far on this site. The show closes with an epic Sugar Mag and great Casey Jones. This stands alone even vs Dane and the following night. The 1977 St Louis is a monster as well and worth grabbing.
